==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[cooin]]'' (modern ''[[coing]]''), from late Latin ''[[malum cotoneum|(malum) cotoneum]]'', a variant of ''[[malum Cydonium]]'' ‘Cydonian apple’, translating Greek [[μήλον κυδώνιον]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kwɪns/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪns|-ɪns]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The pear-shaped [[fruit]] of a small tree of the rose family, ''Cydonia oblonga''.
# The [[deciduous]] [[tree]] bearing such fruit, native to [[Asia]].

